<P>
   CALIF-HOUSE-RACE (Santa Ana, Calif.) _ The calculus of politics
is rapidly changing across California and that is easy to see in
the 46th Congressional District, where old dogs are trying to learn
new tricks to avoid being left behind in this increasingly Hispanic
and Asian district in the heart of Orange County, once a largely
white, conservative bastion. By Don Terry.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients. Photo
[NYT14) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
