<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Don't miss these deals to Europe
 &HT;    By Clara Bosonetto
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   At this time of year airlines offer seemingly perpetual airfare
sales to Europe. Most sales have ticketing deadlines, but they are
often extended from week to week through March.
</P>
<P>
   Saturday is the deadline for a couple of special deals that
deserve a closer look:
</P>
<P>
   Lufthansa offered exclusive discounts to several cities across
Germany that have been matched by a few airlines, which should make
the task of finding space a bit easier.
</P>
<P>
   Round-trip fares of $333 are available to Frankfurt, Stuttgart,
Hamburg and Cologne; Munich, Berlin, Hanover and Nuremberg go for
$363.
</P>
<P>
   Travel is permitted midweek (Monday-Thursday) on departures Nov.
1 through Dec. 11 or Dec. 25 through March 24. Add $30 each way for
Friday-Sunday travel. You must be away at least one Saturday night
and for up to 60 days when traveling with Air France. All other
airlines permit a maximum stay of 30 days. A three-day advance
purchase is required across the board. Travel must be completed by
March 31.
</P>
<P>
   Codes: Lufthansa, WLX1NR; Delta, LLXAN2; Air France, VLXAP3;
Sabena, KLXAN
</P>
<P>
   _ England, Scotland specials: Offered at $368 round trip through
March are London, Manchester and Birmingham, England; and Glasgow,
Scotland.
</P>
<P>
   Midweek departures (Monday-Thursday) are permitted with a
seven-day advance purchase through Dec. 15 or again from Dec.
26-March 24. All travel must be completed by March 31. A weekend
stay is required with all airlines. Remember to purchase your
tickets by Halloween.
</P>
<P>
   Codes: American, MLXSALUK; British Airways, VLXANS98;
Continental, QLX33SE; Delta, LLXSALGB; KLM/Northwest, QLXGB;
United, WLXANS; USAirways, KLXS71E
</P>
<P>
   _ Better sooner than later: A separate sale to other European
destinations also requires ticketing by Saturday. Keep in mind,
though, that these fares are fairly standard for winter travel. If
you must travel overseas in early to mid-November these sale fares
are very good, so go ahead and purchase this week. However, if you
are simply planning a trip after the Christmas-New Year's holidays,
use these rates as a guide and wait for even better deals:
</P>
<P>
   Amsterdam, the Netherlands, is $394 round trip; $398 to
Budapest, Hungary; $408 to Brussels, Belgium and Paris; $416 to
Madrid and Barcelona, Spain, and Lisbon, Portugal; $422 to Warsaw,
Poland; $433 to Prague, Czech Republic; $436 to Rome, Milan, Venice
and Florence, Italy; $438 to Nice and Marseilles, France; $440 to
Zurich and Geneva, Switzerland; $450 to Copenhagen, Denmark, Oslo,
Norway, and Stockholm, Sweden; $544 to Moscow.
</P>
<P>
   Purchase requirements will range from seven- to a three-day
advance (a few airlines require no advance purchase). All airlines
restrict travel at these rates on midweek (Monday-Thursday)
departures through Dec. 17 and again from Dec. 25-March 25. Add
from $20-$30 each way for weekend travel. All travel must be
completed by March 31.
</P>
<P>
   Codes: Air France, VLXSALE4; American, MLXSAAVE; British
Airways, QLXANS7; Continental, QLX36SE; Delta, LLXSL1;
KLM/Northwest, QLXEU16; Lufthansa, WLX4NR; Sabena, BLXSL1;
Swissair, BLXSL1; United, VLXDD; USAirways, KLXS74E.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
