 &HT;    Where to go for the Halloween goodies
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ All the shopping malls listed here offer trick or
treating. Some also have other activities planned. All events are
Saturday; all are free unless noted.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cobb Galleria Centre (U.S. 41 at I-285). Trick or treating, 10
a.m.-8 p.m. Mainstage with Pam &AMP; Buffy, Panorama Steel Band, Wizard
of Odd and others. Hourly costume contests, kid karoke, dinosaur
dig, prizes. $6 ages 2-17; $3 adults.
</P>
<P>
   _ Greenbriar (Langford Parkway at I-285, Atlanta). Trick or
treating, 2:30-7 p.m. Radio Disney 2:30-4:30 p.m. with Curly from
``Goosebumps.'' Free photos in Rich's Court. First 1,000 kids at
Rich's and Burlington Coat Factory receive free trick or treat
bags.
</P>
<P>
   _ North DeKalb (North Druid Hills Road and Lawrenceville
Highway). Trick or treating, 5-8 p.m. Broomhilda the Witch will be
telling stories 7:30-8 p.m. in Clock Court.
</P>
<P>
   _ Northlake (I-285 and Lavista Road, Tucker). Trick or treating,
5:30-7:30 p.m. Magic show with Joseph Daniels in Center Court
7:30-8:15 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ North Point (Haynes Bridge Road, Alpharetta). Trick or
treating, 6-8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ Perimeter (Ashford Dunwoody Road at I-285, Dunwoody). Trick or
treating, 6-8 p.m. Five trick or treat stations throughout the
mall.
</P>
<P>
   _ Shannon Southpark (I-85 and Jonesboro Road). Trick or
treating, 5-7 p.m. Scooby-Doo will be on hand to pose with kids for
photographs.
</P>
<P>
   _ South DeKalb (Candler and Flat Shoals roads). Goodie bags from
Kiss 104.7-FM, noon-3 p.m.; trick-or-treating 6-8 p.m.; Joy Night
Festival and gospel concert in front parking lot, noon-11 p.m.
</P>
