government antitrust trial against Microsoft. By Steve Lohr and
Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-LUXURY (Tokyo) _ Unemployment is at record levels in
Japan, corporate earnings are sinking, bankruptcies are at a record
high, investment is down and the banking system is at the brink of
disaster. But luxury goods retailers are thriving, even as overall
consumer spending is falling. Besides those so wealthy that they
are immune to hard times, it is young working women and even high
school students who are fueling the growth of luxury goods in
Japan. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   AMAZON-EARNINGS (Undated) _ Amazon.com, the Internet book
seller, is to report third-quarter earnings, expected to be a loss
of 59 cents. By Lawrence M. Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   MOTOROLA-SMARTPHONE (Undated) _ Motorola is increasing its
investment in a multinational mobile ``smart phone'' venture with
three European companies _ Nokia, Ericsson and Psion _ that is
important in part because it is avoiding Microsoft technology. By
John Markoff.
</P>
