<HEADER>
A1481 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TEXAS-GHOSTS-2ndTake-     10-28 0632
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEXAS-GHOSTS-2ndTake-TEX </SLUG>
 
FORT WORTH, Texas: staight on end ... 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``A lot of this stuff happened around the stairway. I'd
occasionally hear the flipping of pages, just as if someone had
taken a book and flipped the pages with his thumb. If you know that
sound _ frrrippp _ you can recognize it anywhere ...
</P>
<P>
   ``After careful reflection, I've decided that I believe in
ghosts. It's apparent that it has no intention to do any harm to
me. I think we definitely are hosts to a benign ghost.''
</P>
<P>
   YOU'LL NEVER DINE ALONE: The old Jett Building in downtown Fort
Worth's stylish Sundance Square district is known as the ``Chisholm
Trail Building'' because of the mural of a cattle drive painted on
the outside wall. Built in the early years of the century, the
three-story brick edifice was originally the office of the electric
tram utility. Later, it housed a bookstore and a series of
restaurants.
</P>
<P>
   Unverified reports say it was the site of a suicide in the
1940s, or perhaps a murder, or even multiple murders ...
</P>
<P>
   Mike Leatherwood, who runs several highly successful restaurants
in Dallas and Fort Worth, will remember the location as the site of
two of his eateries that failed within months of opening. ``I just
think the spirits were against us,'' he said. ``Unfortunately,
things were so slow at these restaurants that the hauntings were a
topic of daily conversation.''
</P>
<P>
   Although the Jett long had a reputation of being haunted, Mike
was unaware of it when he took possession in early 1994 ...
</P>
<P>
   Mike and Bill White, one of his partners, were moving items from
the basement to the third floor, a cavernous room with boarded
windows that they planned to use for storage. Mike said the only
access to the upper floors was an old wooden stairway. ``It was a
really neat curved stairway, crooked because it was so old,'' he
said. ``I got up to the third floor and it was pitch black ... I
had a really eerie feeling, like someone was watching me.''
</P>
<P>
   The next day, Bill took an armload of stuff to the top floor,
returning minutes later, severely agitated. ``He said he had to get
out of here,'' Mike recalled. ``And when I asked him why, he said
he had an extremely uncomfortable feeling of having been watched,
of not having been alone. I hadn't told him anything about my
experience.'' Retiring to a nearby restaurant, Mike and Bill were
discussing the strange occurrences when a bartender volunteered
that the building was widely acknowledged to be haunted.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly before one of the restaurants opened, Mike said, the
manager worked into the wee hours writing training manuals. ``It
was about 3 a.m.,'' he said. ``She was working in the basement _
our office was in the basement _ when she heard crashing on the
floor above. She went up to investigate, but when she got to the
first floor, the noise was coming from the second floor. And when
she got to the second floor, it had moved to the third floor. We
had put a wire rack up there to store wine glasses that the
previous restaurant had left and that we weren't going to use.
Well, she stood there watching as the wine glasses crashed one by
one to the floor.''
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps the most frightening event to occur at the Jett happened
to a young restaurant worker. ``She was in the stall of the women's
restroom (in the basement) changing clothes, and there was a song
on our sound tape that she really liked, so she started singing
along with it. Then she heard laughter coming from the adjoining
stall. She thought it was just another employee laughing at her
singing, but the laughter continued. She finished dressing then
peeked through the cracks in the stall door to see who was in
there. It was empty.''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
