<P>
   BLIND MARATHONER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Marathon runner Ricky Cox hopes to be a
winner in this weekend's New York Marathon by slowing down. A
three-time winner of Fort Worth's Cowtown Marathon, Cox, 39, said
he ran the 1983 Boston Marathon in 2 hours, 17 minutes, a time
bordering on world class. Now he figures he'll be a winner in New
York if he finishes the 26.2 miles in 3 hours. This time, he's not
just running. He's serving as a guide for Mike Royal, a runner from
north Fort Worth who also happens to be blind. By PAUL BOURGEOIS.
Story will move in ``a'' national news category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CROSS-UNIFORM &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ The firing of an Arlington, Texas, police
officer who refused to remove a cross from his uniform collar has
attracted the interest of national civil rights groups with vastly
different stances. By JEFF PRINCE. Story will move in ``a''
national news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
