<P>
   GLENN-MISSION (Cape Canaveral, Fla.) _ Preparations for the
launch of the shuttle Discovery are going smoothly, with NASA
officials saying it will be launched as scheduled Thursday with a
historic crewman _ Friendship 7 astronaut John Glenn _ on board. By
MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   GLENN-COLOR (Titusville, Fla.) _ NASA personnel may be trying to
pass this off as just another mission, but if you live anywhere
near the Kennedy Space Center, you know better. Campsites are
overflowing, there's not a hotel room for miles, traffic has slowed
to a crawl and signs wishing astronaut John Glenn Godspeed adorn
many businesses. By KIM COBB and PATTI MUCK.
</P>
<P>
   GLENN-EXPERIMENTS (Cape Canaveral, Fla.) _ A look at the type of
work the crew of shuttle Discovery will be doing after liftoff
Thursday. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPIAN-SUIT (Houston) _ Dominique Moceanu, the 17-year-old
Olympic gymnast who sued to gain independence from her parents,
will join her parents in presenting their out-of-court agreement to
a judge for his approval. By RON NISSIMOV.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-TOWER (Austin) _ The University of Texas' tower, closed to
visitors in 1974 after a number of suicides and the infamous
Charles Whitman sniper murders, will reopen, university officials
say. By JOHN GONZALEZ.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-GOV (Undated) _ While Gov. George W. Bush and his
Democratic opponent, Garry Mauro stump the state, we examine why
Mauro has dropped an important health issue on which he spent $1
million in advertising in the spring and planned to make the
centerpiece of his campaign. By ARMANDO VILLAFRANCA and R.G.
RATCLIFFE.
</P>
