<HEADER>
A1816 &Cx1f; tie-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CIR-MULTI-SITES-NYT &LR;      10-28 0418
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CIR-MULTI-SITES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MULTI-PLAYER ONLINE GAME SITES 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   (italics)Many roads lead to the world of multiplayer games on
line, each offering a different approach. Here are some of the most
popular game destinations:(end italics) &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ULTIMA ONLINE: www.ultimaonline.com A fantasy role-playing game
that was designed from the start by Origin Systems as a multiplayer
game. Ultima is set in an ongoing world, with forests, castles,
villages and taverns, that continues to change even when you are
off line. The only way to play is on the Internet. Ultima Online
is, in essence, its own game center. To play, you must own a copy
of the game, which is about $50, and subscribe to Ultima's online
gaming service, which costs about $9.95 a month.
</P>
<P>
   MYTH: THE FALLEN LORDS: www.bungie.com An adventure role-playing
game by Bungie Software that combines strategy and the hyperspeed
of action games like Quake and Unreal. This game, much like Ultima
Online, is set in an ongoing world, defined by magic and battle.
Playing Myth on the Internet is free through Bungie.net.
</P>
<P>
   GAMES CHANNEL: www.aol.com A game center on America Online that
is strictly for AOL members. Most of the most popular games, like
the virtual card game Spades, can be played at no cost (not
counting AOL's monthly membership fee of $21.95). More advanced
action and adventure games, which AOL groups under the rubric
Xtreme Games, cost $1.99 an hour.
</P>
<P>
   GAME STORM: www.gamestorm.com A classic game center that offers
a wide range of titles and costs $9.99 a month. Some games are
original, like Aliens Online and Godzilla Online. The games are
organized into categories like action, adventure, driving, sports,
strategy, simulation and puzzle and can be downloaded from the site
at no additional cost. Game Storm is a good place for multiplayer
games, like its popular Air Warrior III, a World War II flight
simulation game.
</P>
<P>
   MPATH INTERACTIVE'S MPLAYER.COM: www.mplayer.com A free game
center that permits thousands of players to compete with one
another on the Internet while playing many of the most popular
action and real-time strategy games, like Total Annihilation, Quake
II and Diablo. While Mplayer does not support games with ongoing
universes (like Myth and Ultima), it encourages tournaments and
chat rooms and ranks the best players. Mpath recently added a
premium feature for $3.95 a month that offers some special games
and added support for ratings and rankings.
</P>
