<HEADLINE>
THERE'S MORE THAN ONE WAY TO BREAK IN THOSE JEANS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What does the term ``stonewashed'' mean? _ E.G., Hurst, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Stonewashing is a process of softening denim and other
fabrics to makes them look aged. Stonewashed jeans started to
appear in the United States in 1982.
</P>
<P>
   A July 1, 1994, ``Esquire'' article describes several ways that
manufacturers stonewash jeans: adding pumice stones to the wash
cycle, using cellulase enzymes to ``digest'' the jeans' surface or
tumbling chlorine-soaked pumice stones in the dry cycle.
</P>
<P>
   The process was ``pioneered by the Japanese and French, who were
no doubt inspired by images of peasant women beating their clothes
against river rocks,'' according to ``Esquire.''
</P>
<P>
   If that sounds rough, consider another method of artificially
aging jeans: ``shotgun denim.'' Employees of the Jensen-Smith
company of Chattanooga, Tenn., shot the jeans and sold them with a
spent shell. They sold $1.5 million yearly, which ``would have been
higher if the company had been able to shoot more jeans,''
``Nation's Business'' reported April 1, 1995.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Does Bob Barker have pets of his own? _ L.S., Euless, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Barker, who ends every broadcast of ``The Price is Right'' by
reminding viewers to have pets spayed or neutered, owns a dog named
Federico and a cat named Dulce.
</P>
<P>
   Barker, who began his 27th year as ``Price'' host on Sept. 21,
is active on animal-care issues. In 1988, he stepped down as host
of Miss USA and Miss Universe because organizers awarded fur coats
to winning contestants.
</P>
<P>
   Write to Barker in care of The Price is Right, Price
Productions, 5757 Wilshire Blvd., No. 206, Los Angeles, CA 90036.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Christy Turlington? _ L.E., via the
Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to the model in care of United Talent Agency, 9560
Wilshire Blvd., Suite 500, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   In April, ``BusinessAge'' magazine compiled a list of the
top-earning models. Turlington, who will turn 30 on Jan. 2, was
eighth at $23.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   Last month, model Claudia Schiffer joined Turlington in
withdrawing from the Fashion Cafe chain of restaurants. The venture
was created in 1995 by Schiffer, Turlington, Elle MacPherson and
Naomi Campbell.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
