<P>
   POWER-WALLST _ As a place, Wall Street isn't much more than a
six-block strip of Lower Manhattan running between a graveyard and
a river. But it's also ``the center of the financial universe,''
Worth says in a special report on the history, players and trends
on Wall Street. The report profiles Wall Street's ``20 most
powerful people.'' (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COX-COUPONWEB _ Cox Target Marketing offers shopping coupons
online. Val-Pak will post more than 30,000 coupons at a new Web
site on Thursday. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PHONE-COMPETITION _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Several Austin
small-business owners criticized Southwestern Bell Telephone Co. on
Tuesday for lack of local competition and high in-state
long-distance charges. Their press conference at the Capitol
Marriott Hotel was organized by a local public relations company,
JRG Communications, on behalf of the Partnership for a Competitive
Texas, which was started by AT&AMP;T and other long-distance companies.
(Hight, Austin American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   2
</P>
<P>
   DELL-EXEC-GIFT _ ROUND ROCK, Texas _ In the largest single cash
gift to the arts in Central Texas, five Dell Computer Corp.
executives and their wives have pledged $13 million to help build
the Austin Museum of Art on West Third Street in downtown Austin.
(Mahoney/Barnes, Austin American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETSOLVE-OFFERING _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Despite a cruel and
unforgiving stock market climate, Austin software services company
Netsolve Inc. has filed to make an initial public offering.
(Hawkins, Austin American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   SMALL-BIZ-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ While government agencies and
major corporations have been plowing millions into addressing the
Year 2000 computer issue, many small business owners are just
beginning to look into whether their companies will have problems.
This week the U.S. Small Business Administration is launching a Y2K
Action Week. Next week the Technical Business Network hosts a
conference that explores the legal, insurance and business issues.
We explore the issue, the problems small biz face, and some of the
potential cures. (Tyson, Austin American-Statesman). MOVED
</P>
