finalizing a deal to sell the beleagured downtown landmark to local
businessman Dan O'Leary, who also owns South DeKalb Mall, according
to one of the other bidders. O'Leary, managing partner of
Atlanta-based Capitalist Ventures Inc, is one of three finalists
bidding on Underground, and the first choice of Underground
Festival Inc.'s committee negotiating a deal to present to the
Atlanta City Council. (Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   KENTUCKY-RACE _ ASHLAND, Ky. _ Both parties boast they will make
big gains in Kentucky, where a Senate seat and three House
districts are up for grabs. The campaigns are made more interesting
by the conservative leanings of the Democrats in three out of the
four contests. We'll spend time with Republican Gex (pronounced
Jay) Williams and Democrat Ken Lucas, who are locked in a tight
race. Williams is a client of Georgia's Ralph Reed. (Sherman,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   w/REED-KY _ Washington _ A look at Reed's first crop of
candidates and how they are faring, whether his candidates are
employing similar tactics and how visible Reed himself has been.
(Sherman, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GA-SCHOOLSAFETY _ ATLANTA _ School safety has been, or is, the
subject of a number of recent panels and summits, from a White
House summit Oct. 15 to a state Senate panel that brings its series
of statewide hearings to the Capitol tonight from 7-9 p.m. What
such studies are finding is that school violence, dramatized by a
series of sensational shootings, is relatively rare, but more
everyday problems of disruptive students made for a serious area of
disagreement. Teachers say younger, elementary-age students are
more of a problem than older students, but some parents say they
feel cut off by schools when their child is accused of being
disruptive, especially if race is involved. This experience of many
parents has been heard repeatedly by the panel meeting tonight,
according to convener Sen. Vincent Fort (D-Atlanta) and Suzanne
Dion, a Georgia PTA lobbyist who was also at the local downlink of
the White House summit. (Cumming, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
