<HEADER>
A2146 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TV-SURFER29-COX     10-28 0590
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-SURFER29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    If Lewinsky testifies, all sweeps bets are off
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Oh, what a sweeps this promises to be! Steamy sex all over the
place, dramatic tension, ongoing plot lines involving high stakes,
betrayals and dirty dealings.
</P>
<P>
   And that's just during the House impeachment hearings,
tentatively scheduled to start in mid-November. Although the
networks will pretend it's business as usual, grinding out movies
and ``very special'' series episodes, the real action will be on
Capitol Hill. Let's get real: There is nothing they'll do on ``Ally
McBeal'' or ``ER'' that could compare to Monica Lewinsky testifying
live.
</P>
<P>
   There is, however, nothing resembling a schedule for the
hearings, and there is a schedule for sweeps month, when stations
in about half the country set their ad rates. (In Atlanta, we do it
year-round.) Here are some of the highlights for sweeps, which
start today.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Exposed: Pro Wrestling's Greatest Secrets.'' 8 p.m. EST
Sunday on NBC. Oh no! Don't tell us it's not ... real?
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Oprah Winfrey Presents David and Lisa.'' 9 p.m. EST Sunday
on ABC. An update of the 1962 film about disturbed teens who fall
in love, with Lukas Haas (``Mars Attacks!'') and Brittany Murphy.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Temptations.'' 9 p.m. EST Sunday and Monday on NBC.
Authorized look at the group's history, exploring the way they did
the things they did.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Cats.'' (PBS-check local listings). Andrew Lloyd Webber's
musical was staged for TV for this production.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Mama Flora's Family.'' 9 p.m. EST Nov. 8 and Nov. 10 on
CBS. The final installment in Alex Haley's ``Roots'' saga brings
his family into the 20th century. Cicely Tyson and Queen Latifah
star.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Frank Lloyd Wright.'' (PBS-check local listings). Ken Burns
(``The Civil War'') chronicles the life and career of the architect
over three hours.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Monday After the Miracle.'' 9 p.m. EST Nov. 15 on CBS.
Moira Kelly is the adult Helen Keller and Roma Downey is Annie
Sullivan in this new movie.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Winchell.'' 8 p.m. EST Nov. 21 on HBO. Stanley Tucci (``Big
Night'') plays the gossip columnist.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Saint Maybe.'' 9 p.m. EST Nov. 22 on CBS. Anne Tyler's
novel, starring Mary Louise-Parker, Thomas McCarthy, Edward
Herrmann and Blythe Danner.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Rear Window.'' 9 p.m. EST Nov. 22 on ABC. Christopher Reeve
stars in this remake of the Alfred Hitchcock classic about a man in
a wheelchair man who witnesses a crime.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Late Show With David Letterman Fifth Anniversary Special.''
10 p.m. EST Nov. 23 on CBS. Dave's best.
</P>
<P>
   -- Guest stars. As always, there's a mess of 'em, including Teri
Hatcher on tonight's ``Frasier,'' Laurie Metcalf on ``3rd Rock From
the Sun'' on Nov. 4 and 11, Harvey Korman on ``ER'' on Nov. 5, Hugh
Hefner on the Nov. 6 ``Buddy Faro,'' Sherilyn Fenn on ``Cupid'' on
Nov. 7, gospel star Kirk Franklin on the Nov. 15 ``Sister,
Sister,'' singer David Crosby checking into ``Chicago Hope'' on
Nov. 18.
</P>
<P>
   -- Episodes of note: ``The X-Files'' returns for season six Nov.
8 with a ``mythology'' episode; ``The Drew Carey Show'' goes to
China on Nov. 18, the first American sitcom that has been shot
there; Rev. Camden (Stephen Collins) is shot on Nov. 9's ``7th
Heaven''; ``JAG'' does a thinly veiled take on CNN's ``Operation
Tailwind'' debacle on Nov. 10; and Bobby Simone exits ``NYPD Blue''
on Nov. 17.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: channelsurfer(at)ajc.com
</P>
