<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    This Weekend on TV
 &HT;    By Bob Longino and Lyle V. Harris
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown'' (1966) 8 p.m. EST
on CBS _ Talk about fall classics. This animated feature has our
favorite lovable loser sitting up all night in a pumpkin patch
awaiting the arrival of the great one, and we don't mean Jackie
Gleason.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Snow White: A Tale of Terror'' (1997) 9 p.m. EST on The
Movie Channel _ This made-for-cable remake is not what Walt Disney
had in mind. Sigourney Weaver stars as the evil stepmother in this
truly scary, and very adult, fairy tale about a beautiful orphan
and her vertically challenged co-dependents.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Beetlejuice'' (1988) 9 p.m. EST Comedy Central _ Michael
Keaton is his batty best in the title role as a ghost with an
attitude problem trying to exorcise the living from a creepy
Connecticut homestead. Also stars Alec Baldwin, Geena Davis and
Winona Ryder.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Them!'' (1954) 10 p.m. EST on AMC _ It's a sci-fi movie
about ants the size of Mack trucks. What more could you ask for?
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- Oooh, scary, scary _ Halloween movies for the strong of
heart: 1962's ``Tales of Terror'' with Vincent Price (6:15 p.m. EST
on AMC), 1981's ``An American Werewolf in London'' with David
Naughton (8 p.m. EST on Comedy Central), 1997's ``I Know What You
Did Last Summer'' with Freddie Prinze Jr. (8 p.m. EST on HBO),
1979's ``Dawn of the Dead'' directed by George Romero (midnight EST
on Cinemax) and 1932's ``The Old Dark House'' with Melvyn Douglas
(5:50 a.m. EST on AMC).
</P>
<P>
   -- Oooh, stupid scary _ Halloween movies for the weak of brain:
1980's ``Friday the 13th'' with Betsy Palmer (8 p.m. EST on TNT),
1981's ``Dark Night of the Scarecrow'' with Charles Durning (8:05
p.m. EST on TBS), 1981's ``Friday the 13th, Part 2'' with Amy Steel
(10:20 p.m. EST on TNT), 1987's ``Hellraiser'' directed by Clive
Barker (midnight EST on USA), 1982's ``Friday the 13th, Part 3''
with Dana Kimmell (12:20 a.m. EST on TNT) and 1986's ``King Kong
Lives'' with Brian Kerwin (12:45 a.m. EST on TBS).
</P>
<P>
   -- Oooh, just a bit scary _ Halloween movies for the wee ones:
1993's ``Double, Double, Toil and Trouble'' with the Olsen twins (7
p.m. EST Pax Net), 1966's ``Munster Go Home'' with Fred Gwynne (8
p.m. EST The Family Channel), 1998's ``Scooby-Doo on Zombie
Island'' with the animated wonder dog (8 p.m. EST on Cartoon
Network) and 1966's ``The Ghost and Mr. Chicken'' with Don Knotts
(9 p.m. EST on The Family Channel).
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Temptations'' 9 p.m. EST this day and Monday on NBC _
NBC's two-part movie celebrates the Motown giants but doesn't spare
the drama about drugs and death. Smokey Robinson wrote a new song
that airs during a funeral.
</P>
