 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on. . .NEIL JORDAN (DIRECTOR, ``THE BUTCHER BOY'')
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Company of Wolves'': A twisted, Freudian take on werewolf
stories and Little Red Riding Hood, with Angela Lansbury.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mona Lisa'': Bob Hoskins falls for hooker Cathy Tyson in this
neo-noir film.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Crying Game'': Somebody has a big secret in store for
Irish terrorist Stephen Rea.
</P>
<P>
   ``Interview With the Vampire'': Getting Gothic with Tom Cruise
and Brad Pitt.
</P>
<P>
   ``Michael Collins'': Starring Liam Neeson in an epic account of
the Irish leader.
</P>
