<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, Oct. 29 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact James Laurin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   GENDER-TAX-SURVEY (Los Angeles) _ The price of a nice haircut
and clean clothes for women these days is just too high _
discriminatorily so, according to a California Public Interest
Research Group survey. By Enrique Rivero.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-CLUB-SLUMP (Los Angeles) _ Some of the biggest golf-club
makers have seen sales slide as clubs have gotten bigger, more
high-tech and expensive, so some are getting into the golf-ball
business in search of repeat sales. By Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   NET-PROVIDER-SURVEY (Los Angeles) _ When it comes to the
Internet, the biggest isn't necessarily the best, according to a
survey of Internet service provider customers by J.D. Power and
Associates. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
