<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here is the first of two quizzes oriented toward eating. Match
the literary title with its author. You pass with six correct
answers and earn an A with nine right.
</P>
<P>
   The literary works:
</P>
<P>
   1. ``The Autocrat of the Breakfast Table''
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Babette's Feast''
</P>
<P>
   3. ``Breakfast at Tiffany's''
</P>
<P>
   4. ``Breakfast of Champions''
</P>
<P>
   5. ``Dinner at Eight''
</P>
<P>
   6. ``Dinner at the Homesick Restaurant''
</P>
<P>
   7. ``A Feast of Snakes''
</P>
<P>
   8. ``Guess Who's Coming to Dinner''
</P>
<P>
   9. ``Lunch Poems''
</P>
<P>
   10. ``The Man Who Came to Dinner''
</P>
<P>
   11. ``Naked Lunch''
</P>
<P>
   12. ``Three O'Clock Dinner''
</P>
<P>
   Their authors:
</P>
<P>
   a. William S. Burroughs
</P>
<P>
   b. Truman Capote
</P>
<P>
   c. Harry Crews
</P>
<P>
   d. Isak Dinesen
</P>
<P>
   e. Edna Ferber and George S. Kaufman
</P>
<P>
   f. Moss Hart and George S. Kaufman
</P>
<P>
   g. Oliver Wendell Holmes
</P>
<P>
   h. Frank O'Hara
</P>
<P>
   i. Josephine Pinkney
</P>
<P>
   j. William Rose
</P>
