<HEADER>
A2272 &Cx1f; tic-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MONTINI-COLUMN-AZR &LR;      10-28 0651
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MONTINI-COLUMN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AVOID BARE FACTS ABOUT DR. LAURA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED - I'm trying not to picture Dr. Laura Schlessinger
naked. I'm tempted, but I believe I can resist with the help of Dr.
Laura herself and, of course, the Holy Bible.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Laura has been described as ``America's `Mommy' and the
conscience of talk radio.'' She also has a new book out called
``The TenCommandments.'' The last of the ten, she points out, is
``You shall not covet.''
</P>
<P>
   Lord, I'm trying.
</P>
<P>
   There are nude photographs of Dr. Laura posted on the Internet.
They were made available by a fellow who knew Dr. Laura before she
was rich, famous and nationally syndicated, and says the two of
them used ``to thrash around like a couple of crazed weasels.''
Before she was divorced from her first husband.
</P>
<P>
   According to Dr. Laura's Web site, she ``preaches, teaches and
nags about morals, values and ethics.'' Among these is Commandment
No. 7: ``You shall not commit adultery.''
</P>
<P>
   In her new book, the chapter on No. 7 goes from page 207 to page
234, ending with the declaration:
</P>
<P>
   ``The keeping of our faith with each other and with God is what
separates us from the rest of the animal world.''
</P>
<P>
   Including weasels, I'd guess.
</P>
<P>
   I'd love to steal a look at the photos of the good doctor (begin
ital) au naturel, (end ital) but, as Dr. Laura points out,
Commandment No. 8 says theft of any kind is wrong.
</P>
<P>
   ``Respecting the property and reputation of others provides
mutual safety, peace and prosperity,'' she writes.
</P>
<P>
   I'm sure she's correct.
</P>
<P>
   That's why I haven't looked and urge you not to look. Think of
what your mother would say.
</P>
<P>
   Think of what Dr. Laura's mother would say if she saw the
pictures.
</P>
<P>
   Commandment No. 5 orders you to ``Honor your father and your
mother.'' Although a recent ``Vanity Fair'' magazine article
reported that Dr. Laura ``hasn't seen her own mother in 14 years''
and has been estranged from her sister ``since the 1970s.''
</P>
<P>
   Is mentioning that wrong?
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Laura didn't dispute the claims so technically they don't
fall under Commandment No. 9's order not to bear false witness.
</P>
<P>
   Neither does looking at the photographs, unless they were faked
or altered.
</P>
<P>
   Or unless they were taken by a peeping Tom instead of a smiling
Bill (the name of the man who claims to be her former lover).
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Laura got a restraining order against the man who
distributed the pictures. Others copied them, however, and posted
them on their own. Her lawyers will probably try to stop those
people, too.
</P>
<P>
   This is possible when you sell your radio show, as Dr. Laura
did, for a reported $71.5 million, and expect to make millions more
explaining the Ten Commandments.
</P>
<P>
   Including No. 2.
</P>
<P>
   That one urges us not to worship false gods, like money and
possessions, which Dr. Laura, who lives a life of luxury, says
``are not the ultimate purpose of life.''
</P>
<P>
   In the end, it's not the Commandments that will keep me from
picturing Dr. Laura naked, however.
</P>
<P>
   It's Dr. Laura's most famous slogan:
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm my kid's mom.''
</P>
<P>
   Schlessinger and her husband have a son, Deryk.
</P>
<P>
   As tempting as it is to expose the bare facts about Dr. Laura,
to discover if full frontal nudity would reveal, once and for all,
her two faces _ there is this boy to consider.
</P>
<P>
   It's tough enough on him knowing the pictures exist and have
become public.
</P>
<P>
   It's nothing he asked for. It's nothing he did. It's nothing he
can escape.
</P>
<P>
   Even if she deserves what she gets, he doesn't.
</P>
<P>
   Just ask a well-known Stanford co-ed whose mom and dad live in a
mansion in Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   That's why I'm shying away from the naughty pictures. Not
because Dr. Laura is her kid's mom, but because Deryk is his mom's
kid. &QL; 
 &QL; 
E.J. Montini can be reached at ed.montini(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
