</P>
<P>
   Parents who complained about feeling shut off by the schools
contradicts a common refrain from educators and even some parents
who blame the parents of disruptive students for not being
involved, Dion said. ``The majority of schools do not know what
parent involvement means,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Sen. Vincent Fort (D-Atlanta), chairman of the study committee,
said that ``from the testimony we have heard, there seems to be a
genuine concern that there is a need for more teacher training and
focus on class management.'' Additionally, he said, ``And our
minority students are disparately impacted when it comes to
excessive disciplinary actions.''
</P>
<P>
   The hearing is 7-9 p.m. in Room 450 of the Capitol.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
