</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-TOWER (Austin, Texas) _ The University of Texas' tower,
closed to visitors in 1974 after a number of suicides and the
infamous Charles Whitman sniper murders, will reopen, university
officials say. By JOHN GONZALEZ. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-GOV (Undated) _ While Gov. George W. Bush and his
Democratic opponent, Garry Mauro stump the state, we examine why
Mauro has dropped an important health issue on which he spent $1
millionin advertising in the spring and planned to make the
centerpiece of his campaign. By ARMANDO VILLAFRANCA and R.G.
RATCLIFFE.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   NBA-LOCKOUT (Undated) _ The National Basketball Association
cancels two additional weeks of games, adding to the toll the
lockout has taken on the league. By MICHAEL MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BAYLOR (Waco, Texas) _ It will be an interesting reunion
this weekend when Baylor coach Dave Roberts takes his team to South
Bend, Ind., to take on nationally ranked Notre Dame and Roberts'
former colleague, Irish head coach Bob Davie. By DANNY ROBBINS.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Independence, Mo.) _ If office seekers behind
in the polls are looking for a shrine to election-year miracles,
they will find it here at 219 North Delaware St. This is where
Harry Truman lived, and his surprise victory over Thomas Dewey set
the standard for projected losers who become ultimate winners. By
ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Already filed.)
</P>
