<SLUG> BC-BUBBLE-CHAMP-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TURN ON DA BUBBLE MACHINE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LARRY BINGHAM 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   There are kids who blow bubbles, and then there are kids who
blow bubbles _ bubbles huge enough to score them a free trip to New
York and tickets to the World Series and a telephone call from Jay
Leno's people.
</P>
<P>
   Just ask Justin Dunaway. Thirteen year-old Justin, who lives in
the Dallas suburb of Coppell, finished fifth in the Bubble Yum
World Series Blowout. Some kid from Cleveland won, but who cares?
</P>
<P>
   So, Justin, how long have you been blowing bubbles?
</P>
<P>
   ``I think since I was about 7 or 8.''
</P>
<P>
   What's your favorite?
</P>
<P>
   ``Bubble Yum.''
</P>
<P>
   Favorite flavor?
</P>
<P>
   ``Strawberry.
</P>
<P>
   What do you recommend for the biggest bubbles?
</P>
<P>
   ``Probably just a little cheap brand, because I had some the
other night, at this parade I was at, and I was blowing like
humongous bubbles ... I might have a piece right here. Hold on. On
the wrapper it says Swell Bubble Gum, so Swell works good.''
</P>
<P>
   What makes it good for big bubbles?
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know. I was just like blowing a few bubbles with it
and they were all really, really big, like bigger than any ones
I've blown before.''
</P>
<P>
   Do you experiment with gum?
</P>
<P>
   ``In science, I did a science experiment on gum. I said, `Which
can blow bigger bubbles _ sugar or sugarless gum?' And I used
Bubble Yum, Bubblicious and umm, Bazooka as the sugar gum, and I
used Carefree, Trident and Wintergreen for the sugarless gum, and
it turned out that sugarless blows bigger bubbles.''
</P>
<P>
   Sugarless?
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah, because in sugar gum, you have to chew it to get the
sugar out of it, and sugarless gum, the sugar is already out, so
you go straight to blowing bubbles.''
</P>
<P>
   Is there a correlation between number of pieces and bubble size?
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah. Like if you have a ton, like eight or nine pieces of
gum, the wad of gum is too big so it won't blow a bubble, or it's
really hard to chew. If you have five or six, you can blow really
good bubbles.''
</P>
<P>
   Anything else we should do to blow bubbles like you?
</P>
<P>
   ``Umm, just work hard and don't give up.''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
