<HEADLINE>
PROFILE OF NEW YORK GOV. GEORGE PATAKI 
</HEADLINE>
   (With NY-PATAKI-PROFILE) 
 (nk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   PROFILE: George Elmer Pataki &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BORN: June 24, 1945, Peekskill, N.Y. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HOME: Garrison, N.Y. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION: Peekskill High School, 1963; B.A., Yale University,
1967; J.D., Columbia Law School, 1970.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CAREER: Law firm of Dewey, Ballantine, Bushby, Palmer &AMP; Wood,
1970-74; law firm of Plunkett &AMP; Jaffe, 1974-84; Mayor of Peekskill,
N.Y., 1982-84; New York State Assembly, 1985-92; New York State
Senate, 1993-94; Governor of New York, 1995-present. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY: Libby Rowland Pataki, wife; four children, Emily, 19,
Teddy, 16, Allison, 13, Owen, 11.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   INTERESTS: Reading history, hiking, basketball. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
