<SLUG> BC-BKC-TAAC29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ga. State picked to win the TAAC
 &HT;    By Earnest Reese
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ When the Trans America Athletic Conference held its
annual basketball media-day event in Atlanta on Wednesday, two
coaches from a year ago were conspicious by their absence. Shakey
Rodriguez of Florida International and John Kresse of College of
Charleston have taken their teams to other leagues.
</P>
<P>
   Those changes explain in parts why Georgia State, in Lefty
Driesell's second year as coach, has been picked by league coaches
and sports information directors to win the TAAC title this season.
</P>
<P>
   The 66-year-old Driesell, seated next to former Georgia coach
and TAAC newcomer Hugh Durham on the podium at the gathering,
seemed unfazed by the vote.
</P>
<P>
   ``It doesn't mean a thing to be picked No. 1 in the preseason,
although I'd rather be picked first than last,'' he said. ``It's
still going to depend on what kind of coaching job you do.''
</P>
<P>
   The job Driesell and his staff did last season produced a
school-record 16 victories and left the veteran coach one win
shortof 700 heading into the Nov. 18 opener against Georgetown in
the Georgia Dome.
</P>
<P>
   However, only two starters return from last year, and senior
forward Quincy Gause recently was declared academically ineligible
for fall semester.But that game also marks the resumption of
basketball careers for former Georgia Tech point guard Kevin Morris
and off guard Anton Reese, who started at Alabama two years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Durham, who has compiled a record of 536-330 during his 30 years
in the business, is one of two new coaches introduced. His
Jacksonville University team _ not to be confused with TAAC member
Jacksonville State of Alabama _ joins the 11-team league from the
Sun Belt Conference.
</P>
<P>
   The other newcomer is Jacksonville State coach Mark Turgeon, who
played for Larry Brown at Kansas ('83-'87) and comes from an
assistant's position with Brown's Phiadelphia 76ers.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
