<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-28 22:20 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2586 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-FALNOTE29-COX     10-28 0859
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALNOTE29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Falcons starting defense hit hard by injuries
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Falcons (5-2) have the NFL's No. 5 defense against
the run, allowing 90.1 yards per game, but that number could be in
jeopardy Sunday against the Rams (2-5) if the team's infirm list
doesn't improve.
</P>
<P>
   Starting DTs Travis Hall and Shane Dronett, and MLB Jessie
Tuggle did not practice Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Hall missed Sunday's Jets game with a bruised knee. Dronett tore
the plantar fascia muscle completely free from the bone in his his
foot against New York, where Tuggle suffered a high ankle sprain.
</P>
<P>
   All are questionable, although Tuggle appears least critical.
</P>
<P>
   Hall is having problems pushing off. Dronett's injury, which is
similar to the one that has sidelined Georgia Tech flanker Jon
Muyres for the entire season, is causing great soreness, but, he
said, not much loss of function.
</P>
<P>
   Starting left DE Lester Archambeau (strained thumb), who leads
the team with 4.5 sacks and is third with 46 tackles (behind LB
Cornelius Bennett's 59 and Tuggle's 50), could start for Hall,
making John Burrough the starter at LDE.
</P>
<P>
   Esera Tuaolo would start for Dronett on a defense that already
will have second-year CB Michael Booker starting for injured Ronnie
Bradford.
</P>
<P>
   On the plus side, Henri Crockett, who was starting strongside LB
before dislocating his left wrist Sept. 13 against the Eagles,
returned to practice. He was Tuggle's backup before, and worked at
MLB Wednesday. If Tuggle can't play, though, Ruffin Hamilton would
probably start.
</P>
<P>
   Help wanted
</P>
<P>
   Looking for depth, and perhaps a right gunner for the punting
team, the Falcons Monday put in a claim on CB Rod Smith, who was
waived by Carolina. Green Bay also put in a claim. Since both the
Packers and Falcons are 5-2, there was a coin toss. Atlanta lost.
On Tuesday, Atlanta put in a waiver claim on CB Juran Bolden,
waived earlier this year by the Falcons and waived Monday by the
Packers. He was claimed, however, by Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   Good news on Chandler
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Chris Chandler looked and felt great Wednesday after
his first full practice since straining his non-throwing shoulder
and bruising ribs Oct. 18 against the Saints.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel a lot stronger,'' he said, ``and it's improved a lot
after 10 days of rest and treatment.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think I'll be ready to go (Sunday).''
</P>
<P>
   Musical chairs
</P>
<P>
   Coach Dan Reeves said WRs Todd Kinchen and Jammi German will
replace Tim Dwight (sprained knee) in the ``H'' position, but the
team will not put in any special plays for them, like it did for
Dwight.
</P>
<P>
   Kinchen played the first two games, but then was inactive for
three of four before catching three passes against the Jets. He
insists a rift between him and Reeves, which began in the season
opener when the coach got on the seven-year veteran after he
attempted a lateral, is patched up.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a very demanding coach, and I would be, too,'' Kinchen
said. ``I made some mental errors at the beginning of the year when
I wasn't focused.''
</P>
<P>
   Kinchen will replace Dwight as punt returner.
</P>
<P>
   On kickoff returns, rookie CB Elijah Williams will become the
primary return man, and will be joined either by German or rookie
RB Ken Oxendine.
</P>
<P>
   The mystery continues regarding RB Harold Green, who has been
inactive five straight games.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, he usually joined RB Byron Hanspard (who's out for
the season with a knee injury) deep on kickoffs. He also was the
team's premier third-down back and third-leading receiver, with 29
catches for 360 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Reeves has said Green has been de-activated because he doesn't
play special teams and Oxendine does. Oxendine dressed but did not
play the past two games.
</P>
<P>
   When asked why Green isn't practicing with special teams, even
as a backup, special teams coach Joe DeCamillis said it was because
Green isn't going to be active.
</P>
<P>
   Green said he's willing to play special teams and doesn't know
of anything he's done wrong.
</P>
<P>
   ``I hope it's not a situation where they think I won't play
special teams,'' he said. ``I pride myself on doing my job.''
</P>
<P>
   Extra points
</P>
<P>
   St. Louis third-down back Amp Lee, who broke a hand Sunday,
won't play, and TE Ernie Conwell (torn knee ligaments) is out for
the season. Rookie TE Roland Williams (two catches, 13 yards) will
start. Also missing Rams practice Wednesday: WR Isaac Bruce
(strained hamstring), LT Orlando Pace (bruised shoulder), G Mike
Gruttadauria (back spasms), G Zach Wiegert (hyperextended knee) and
G Ryan Tucker (neck). ... The Falcons Wednesday worked out DT Ed
Jasper (6-foot-2, 295), a second-year player released last week by
the Eagles. ... Ticket sales for Sunday's game are dismal, as there
have been just about 37,000 sold. That's become a trend. Atlanta
sold fewer tickets for the Rams game in each of the last two years
than any other: Just 36,583 last year, and 26,519 in '96. The
Dolphins had sold out every home game for more than two years until
the Rams played there two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
