<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TROJANS HOPING TO UNCROSS SIGNALS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The big decision for USC coach Paul Hackett this
week isn't who to start at quarterback but how to signal plays into
the game.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett is considering having the quarterbacks wear wristbands
or sending a receiver with the play, to ease the process with which
the offense receives the information.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant coach Ken O'Brien has signaled plays into the
quarterback all season, but USC has burned timeouts and received
delay-of-game penalties in critical situations because of frequent
confusion.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans lost a touchdown pass to Mike Bastianelli against
Oregon because the 25-second clock had expired. A similar penalty
nullified a long pass to R. Jay Soward against Florida State.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's something we've been looking into,'' Hackett said about
having the quarterbacks wear wristbands. ``I've been hesitant to
change. I think we might take the pressure off them. We haven't
made a decision yet.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said he is also mulling the possibility of having a
receiver run the plays in to the huddle. Hackett said he would
prefer to continue signaling in the plays.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're a whisker away from saying things are working very
well,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Powell gets the start: Fullback Marvin Powell will get his
second straight start this week. At left guard, there is still a
battle between last week's starter, Donta Kendrick, and Jason
Grain.
</P>
<P>
   ``No one's going to get into a comfort zone,'' offensive line
coach Steve Greatwood said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Hopeful but realistic: The Trojans are trying to remain
positive despite recognizing that the team's Rose Bowl hopes are
all but eliminated.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a lot of games left. You can win the four games that
are left and go 9-3,'' linebacker Chris Claiborne said. ``Right
now, it doesn't look like we're going to do it, but we've got a
chance.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've put ourselves in a position to make us work harder than
we have to.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Tapering down: USC practiced in shorts Wednesday, because
Hackett felt the Trojans are physically banged up.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive tackle Aaron Williams is day-to-day with a neck
stinger, but Hackett expects him to play. Shamsud-Din Abdul-Shaheed
has moved from end to tackle and will start if Williams can't play.
</P>
<P>
   __ Thomas cleared to practice: Freshman quarterback Jason Thomas
practiced in pads for the first time since undergoing ankle
surgery. Thomas played scout-team quarterback. Also practicing for
the first time in several weeks was Quincy Woods, who has had a
swollen knee.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive tackle Marc Matock underwent X-rays Tuesday, which
revealed that his broken ankle is healing as scheduled. Matock said
he hopes to return for the UCLA game.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-28-98 2327EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
