<SLUG> BC-BKC-CSNHOOP-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CARR, CROWE FIGHT TO MAKE THEIR POINT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Like a car with plugged fuel injectors, the Cal
State Northridge's men's basketball team was prone to stops, starts
and sputters. That's what happens when a team doesn't have a true
point guard.And, it's why the Matadors are expecting a dramatic
improvement.
</P>
<P>
   Last season the Matadors had no point guard, just a guard
playing the point. This year they have Markus Carr and Jason Crowe,
both recruited as point guards. For two weeks they battled in
practice, and it will continue for a little more time.
</P>
<P>
   Carr, a 6-foot-1 redshirt freshman from Palmdale High, was
picked as the point guard last season until a knee injury wrecked
his year before it began. He's the favorite to start.
</P>
<P>
   ``Having Jason come in and compete with me every day is good
practice for me, and for him,'' Carr said.
</P>
<P>
   Crowe, a 6-4 transfer from American University, also spent last
year sitting on the sideline because of Division I transfer rules.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel, at this point, if I do what I'm supposed to do, I will
be the starter,'' Crowe said. ``Markus probably feels the same way.
He's a competitive kid who's not going to back down. We're very
competitive, but we have a good relationship off the court. We
chit-chat and hang out together.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Counting Crowe's eligibility: Braswell said CSUN will
petition the NCAA for another year of eligibility for Crowe. He's
listed as a junior but has only three semesters of eligibility
remaining, which must be used concurrently.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're trying to find out if there's a way he can get another
semester of eligibility,'' Braswell said. ``His clock runs out at
the end of the next semester. If that wasn't the case, I would hold
him out of (next fall) so he could play in January.''
</P>
<P>
   Braswell said the school is in the first stages of formulating
the appeal.
</P>
<P>
   Before attending CSUN, Crowe attended Wayne State, then Los
Angeles Trade Technical College and American University.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jason's in the process of contacting the university where he
officially started because he actually dropped out of a couple
classes and he thought his enrollment was under full-time status.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Exhibition opener nears: Just two weeks after beginning
official practices, CSUN will get a better look at where it stands
with an exhibition game against the California All-Stars on Sunday
at 4 p.m.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
